# Always push to main and Vercel

After completing code or config changes to this project:

1. Stage and commit the changed files (use a clear commit message).
2. Push to the remote: `git push origin main`.

The project is deployed on Vercel from the GitHub repo; pushing to `main` triggers a new deployment. Always push to `main` so Vercel redeploys. Do not skip the push step unless the user asks not to deploy.
